## UI Architecture & Recent Overhaul

We recently discarded the legacy Bootstrap/CSS architecture in favor of a modern, pure Tailwind CSS setup. The UI was designed using **Stitch by Google** (Project ID: 3697614804123319091) and carefully extracted into Blazor.

**Tech Stack**: Blazor WASM (.NET 9), Tailwind CSS (via CDN), Google Fonts (Inter, Hanken Grotesk, JetBrains Mono), and Material Symbols.

### State Management
- **`TurnFillDataService.cs`**: An in-memory scoped service providing mock `Resource` and `RosterParticipant` data to simulate real-time UI interactions without a backend. 

### Key Screens & Components
- **`Index.razor` (Dashboard)**: Dynamic bento-grid dashboard showing resource health bars.
- **`ResourceDetail.razor`**: Detailed view displaying depletion line charts (SVG) and roster sequences.
- **`RosterManagement.razor`**: Drag-and-drop styled roster manager and rotation visualizer.
- **`MainLayout.razor`**: Fixed top/bottom app bars with dynamic routing highlighting.
- **`AddNewResourceOverlay.razor`**: A right-side slide-over modal for creating new resources.
- **`RefillActionOverlay.razor`**: A bottom-sheet modal to confirm refills and advance rosters.

